u(x_0,0,0,t_0)
\psi
\alpha t_0/2 + x_0
\alpha t_0 \psi_x
x = \frac{t_0}{\sqrt{t_0^2-x_0^2}} (\frac{\alpha}{2}\sqrt{t_0^2-x_0^2})+\frac{x_0}{\sqrt{t_0^2-x_0^2}}\sqrt{t_0^2-x_0^2}=t_0 \alpha/2  +x_0
\chi_{x'} = \psi_{x'} = \psi_x \frac{\partial x}{\partial x'} = \frac{t_0}{\sqrt{t_0^2-x_0^2}} \psi_x 
\alpha t_0 \psi_x
